# Safety: No Destructive Commands

Hard rules for this repository:

- Never run database reset/destructive commands.
- Never run destructive git commands.
- Never run any remote Git/Supabase command automatically.
- Require explicit user confirmation before any risky operation.

## Forbidden commands

- `supabase db reset`
- `supabase db wipe`
- `supabase db drop`
- `supabase migration repair` (unless user explicitly asks for it)
- `psql ... DROP DATABASE ...`
- `git reset --hard`
- `git checkout --`
- `git clean -fd`
- any command containing `DROP SCHEMA`, `DROP DATABASE`, `TRUNCATE` in production

## Remote operations (strict allowlist)

The agent must treat the following as remote/risky and NEVER run them unless the user explicitly asks in the same message:

- Any `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, `git clone`, `gh *`
- Any `supabase link`, `supabase db push`, `supabase db reset`, `supabase functions deploy`
- Any command using `--linked` or `--project-ref`

If not explicitly requested, do not execute.

## Risky operations policy

Before running any operation that can modify remote data (database, auth users, migrations, deployment), the agent must:

1. Explain exactly what will run.
2. Ask for explicit confirmation in one message.
3. Run only the confirmed command.

If the user does not explicitly confirm, do not execute.
